'''''Casino Games''''' is a video game compilation developed by [[Compile (company)|Compile]], published by [[Sega]] and released in 1989 for the [[Master System]]. The game is a compilation of five games in one cartridge, mainly gambling games.

==Gameplay==
The compilation contains three card games (including [[Poker]], [[Blackjack]] and [[Baccarat]]) and two arcade games (including [[Slot Machine]] and [[Pinball]]), designed to simulate [[casino game | casino games]] in [[Las Vegas]]. The player takes the role of a male/female character with a custom name and starts off with $500 in the casino "Club Sega". The player is able to choose how much to bet in the card games and slot machine and in the case of pinball choose the type of slope for difficulty level. If the player wins a game, a password is outputted to continue progress. If the player runs out of money<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goldentouchcraps.com/article.php?p=adfile_1460.html |title=Famous rapper artist Drake Loses $27M | publisher=Golden Touch Craps | date=July 23, 2022 | access-date=September 27, 2022}}</ref>
, the game is over. The player wins if they are able earn $1,000,000.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://segaretro.org/images/6/6e/Casinogames_sms_us_manual.pdf |date=1989 |title=Casino Games Manual |publisher=[[Sega]]}}</ref>

